.TH AADK 1 "April 2026" "AADK" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aadk \- start the AADK services and GTK interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aadk
[\fB--services\fR]
[\fIui-args\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aadk
starts the AADK background services and, by default, launches the GTK4 user
interface.
.PP
The command is the packaged entry point for the Debian build and resolves to
the installed launcher under
.IR /usr/lib/aadk/bin/aadk-start .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --services
Start the gRPC services without launching the GTK UI.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show the launcher help text and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/aadk/logs
Runtime logs written by the launcher and packaged services.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aadk-ui (1),
.BR aadk-cli (1)
